chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.
chunks.plain_content:
Peripheral arterial disease and driving
You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.

chunks.html_content: You don’t need to tell DVLA if you have peripheral arterial disease.
chunks.plain_content:
Peripheral arterial disease and driving
Car or motorcycle licence
You don’t need to tell DVLA if you have peripheral arterial disease.

chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA if you have peripheral arterial disease. Fill in form VOCH1 and send it to the address on the form.
chunks.plain_content:
Peripheral arterial disease and driving
Bus, coach or lorry licence
You must tell DVLA if you have peripheral arterial disease. Fill in form VOCH1 and send it to the address on the form.
